Text: State media reported over the weekend that the Hangzhou Municipal Government would transfer 100 representatives to key enterprises such as Alibaba, Geely Holdings and Wahaha. A full list of the 100 companies included in the initiative was not released. The directive, which media said was part of the Hangzhou government's New Manufacturing Plan, is reportedly an attempt to boost manufacturing and bolster the local economy in the eastern province of Zhejiang.
